org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.phd

Interface PhdWholeReadItem


  • public interface PhdWholeReadItem
    PhdWholeReadItem is specially formatted optional additional information about an entire phd record. WholeReadItems can be used by Phrap/Consed to process reads differently. For example, some whole read items designate which reads are mate pairs or which reads have faked data. WholeReadItems contain free form text that will vary by what kind of data is provided and which program is producing or consuming these tags so a generic PhdWholeReadItem object can only provide the free form data as Strings.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • getLines

        List<String> getLines()
        Get a list of all the lines contained in this WholeReadItem. Each String may still contain whitespace or end of line data.
        Returns:
        a list of Strings, one for each line in the read item; if no lines exist for this item, then an empty list will be returned; will never return null.
